review_comments:
["`getExtensionPromptFiles` no longer evaluates contributed `when` clauses and instead returns all extension-contributed prompt paths. For prompt/skill this is later re-evaluated via the propagated `when`, but for types like `agent` and `instructions` the `when` is not propagated onto `ICustomAgent`/`IInstructionFile`, so the contribution-level `when` will effectively be ignored (agents/instructions will always be enabled). Consider either keeping `when` filtering for those types here, or carrying a parsed `when` expression through the discovery results and filtering with a scoped context at the consumption site.

See below for a potential fix:
```
	private shouldFilterContributedWhenAtDiscovery(type: PromptsType): boolean {
		switch (type) {
			case PromptsType.agent:
			case PromptsType.instructions:
				return true;
			default:
				return false;
		}
	}

	private async getExtensionPromptFiles(type: PromptsType, token: CancellationToken): Promise<IExtensionPromptPath[]> {
		await this.extensionService.whenInstalledExtensionsRegistered();
		const settledResults = await Promise.allSettled(this.contributedFiles[type].values());
		const shouldFilterWhenAtDiscovery = this.shouldFilterContributedWhenAtDiscovery(type);
		// Note: `when` clauses are deferred for contribution types that propagate them
		// to later session-scoped evaluation. For types like agents and instructions,
		// the contribution-level `when` must still be enforced here because it is not
		// carried through discovery results.
		const contributedFiles = settledResults
			.filter((result): result is PromiseFulfilledResult<IExtensionPromptPath> => result.status === 'fulfilled')
			.map(result => result.value)
			.filter(file => {
				if (!file.when) {
					return true;
				}

				const whenExpr = ContextKeyExpr.deserialize(file.when);
				if (!whenExpr) {
					this.logger.warn(`[getExtensionPromptFiles] Ignoring contributed prompt file with invalid when clause: ${file.when}`);
					return false;
				}

				if (!shouldFilterWhenAtDiscovery) {
					return true;
				}

				return this.contextKeyService.contextMatchesRules(whenExpr);
```", "Avoid hardcoding `'local'` here; there is already a `localChatSessionType` constant. Using the shared constant prevents future drift if the value changes and keeps session-type checks consistent across the chat code.", 'This new default-local-only behavior for skills in non-local sessions (and the new `when` evaluation path) isn’t covered by tests in `computeAutomaticInstructions.test.ts`. Please add coverage for at least: (1) non-local session excludes skills without `when`, and (2) skills with a `when` that matches the scoped context remain included.', 'already listens to `when`', '## Pull request overview

Adjusts how extension-contributed prompt “when” clauses are handled so availability can be determined in a session-scoped context (e.g., per chat widget / session type), rather than using the global context at discovery time.

**Changes:**
- Stop evaluating contributed prompt file `when` clauses in `PromptsService.getExtensionPromptFiles` (validate only), deferring evaluation to later.
- Propagate contributed `when` clauses into slash command and skill models so consumers can evaluate them in scoped contexts.
- Default skills without a `when` clause to local-session-only in `ComputeAutomaticInstructions`, based on `chatSessionType`.

### Reviewed changes

Copilot reviewed 3 out of 3 changed files in this pull request and generated 3 comments.

| File | Description |
| ---- | ----------- |
| src/vs/workbench/contrib/chat/common/promptSyntax/service/promptsServiceImpl.ts | Defers `when` evaluation and starts propagating `when` into slash commands/skills. |
| src/vs/workbench/contrib/chat/common/promptSyntax/computeAutomaticInstructions.ts | Filters skills by session type (local vs non-local) and evaluates skill `when` per session. |
| src/vs/workbench/contrib/chat/browser/widget/input/editor/chatInputCompletions.ts | Hides extension-provided prompt slash commands in locked-agent mode unless `when` references `chatSessionType`. |



']

